\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 14. P. prolifera }(L.) P.W. Ball & Heywood,{\i  op. cit.} 161 (1964) ({\i Dianthus prolifer} L., {\i Tunica prolifera} (L.) Scop., {\i Kohlrauschia prolifera} (L.) Kunth). Up to 50 cm, glabrous or scabrid-pubescent. Leaf-sheaths usually about as long as wide. Largest bracts 6-12 × 3-7(-8) mm, usually obtuse, mucronate. Petals 10-14 × 2-3·5 mm, pink with darker veins; limb obcordate. Seeds 1·3-1·9 × 0·8-1·1 mm, reticulate, with strongly incurved sides. 2n = 30.{\i  C. & S. Europe, extending northwards to S. Sweden, westwards to C. Spain and eastwards to Krym.} Al Au Be Bu Co Cz Da Ga Ge Gr He Ho Hs Hu It Ju Po Rm Rs(C, W, K) Sa Si Su Tu [*Br].
