\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 16. P. velutina }(Guss.) P.W. Ball & Heywood,{\i  op. cit. }166 (1964) ({\i Dianthus velutinus} Guss., {\i Tunica velutina }(Guss.) Fischer & C.A. Meyer, {\i Kohlrauschia velutina} (Guss.) Reichenb.). Very like {\b 14} but the middle part of the stem usually densely glandular-tomentose; leaf-sheaths at least twice as long as wide; all outer bracts acute or mucronate; petal-limb 1·2-2·5 mm wide; seeds 1-1·3 × 0·7-0·8 mm, with cylindrical papillae. 2n = 30.{\i  S. Europe.} Al Bu Co Cr Ga Gr Hs It Ju Lu Sa Si Tu.
